{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The high level people came-- we believe Himmler actually came to Belsen, and that he was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We saw some high level people in staff cars and big leather coats, and all that sort of thing-- this was before Kramer, in something like June '44-- came to supervise the exchange, and Red Cross people, and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So, yeah, it looked good.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it obviously gave us hope that one day we might be exchanged.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in fact, there was another exchange early in 1945 of mainly American people with American connections, we believe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But we, again, were not called.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it did give us hope in that we realized that there was still a possibility that we might get exchanged.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But early '45 things really got bad, because then the typhus fever started.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And people were dying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In 1944, relatively few people, apparently, died in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The numbers were not large in our camp of 4,000.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I think altogether in Belsen, there was about 15,000 people there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But in the early month of '45, it swelled to 60,000, or something like that, people, I understand.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And it really got very, very crowded in Belsen with all these people who were transferred from the East, who had been in Auschwitz and other camps, and who'd been on long train journeys, and lots of other camps, and on death marches, and all that.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they all came to Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Then, you know, we got the lice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So that was one of the pastimes that I remember very well, that we spent hours and hours every day hunting the lice.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We used to take all our clothes off and get them [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They congregate in your hair.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
